# Documentation Rules

## When to update docs

| Change | Update |
|--------|--------|
| New MVP feature | Check off item in `system-requirements.md` |
| New approved technology | `tech-stack.md` |
| Architectural fork | New ADR in `docs/adr/` |
| Folder layout change | `README.md` Project Structure section |

## ADR format

Number sequentially: `00N-short-title.md`. Each ADR includes:

1. Context / problem
2. **Decision** (bold)
3. **Tradeoff**
4. **Alternatives** with accept/reject rationale

Link related docs: `[system requirements](../system-requirements.md)`, `[queue tool](001-queue-tool.md)`.

## Do not add

- Outdated architecture PNGs — use mermaid in README or prose in ADRs
- Duplicate tech stack lists — link to `tech-stack.md` instead
